  "handle": "patelar",
  "title": "Patelar",
  "body": "<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div data-state=\"active\" data-orientation=\"horizontal\" role=\"tabpanel\" aria-labelledby=\"radix-:r1mr:-trigger-default\" id=\"radix-:r1mr:-content-default\" tabindex=\"0\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div dir=\"auto\" id=\"markdown-content-2\">\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<h1>Patelar – Vidheyan Bhaskara Patelar Tribute Tee</h1>\n<h3>Mammootty's most terrifying performance. Ever.</h3>\n<p>Some roles haunt you forever. Bhaskara Patelar from Vidheyan (1994) is Mammootty at his most terrifying – a National Award-winning portrayal of absolute power corruption as the tyrannical landlord who breaks every moral boundary. Directed by Adoor Gopalakrishnan and adapted from Paul Zacharia's novella, the film explores the sick master-slave relationship between Patelar and his obedient servant Thommy in rural Karnataka.</p>\n<p>Patelar doesn't just demand loyalty – he destroys lives. Thommy kills his own wife on Patelar's orders, watches helplessly as Patelar violates his family, and escorts his master through the jungle like a pet even after Patelar murders his own wife Saroja. This tee honors one of Malayalam cinema's darkest, most unforgettable villains – a performance so intense it won Mammootty the National Award for Best Actor.</p>\n<p>Printed on premium 100% cotton with Petrocrib's signature relaxed unisex fit. Perfect for parallel cinema enthusiasts, Mammootty collectors, and anyone who respects when Malayalam cinema goes fearlessly dark. Wear it to film festivals, retrospective screenings, or serious movie discussions where superficial mass heroes don't belong.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div>\n<div><br></div>\n<div>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Tribute to Mammootty's National Award-winning Bhaskara Patelar from <em>Vidheyan</em> (1994)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Based on Adoor Gopalakrishnan's master-slave power dynamic masterpiece</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Adapted from Paul Zacharia's novella <em>Bhaskara Pattelarum Ente Jeevithavum</em></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>100% premium cotton – soft, breathable, built to last</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Relaxed unisex fit for collectors and cinema enthusiasts</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Serious parallel cinema tribute, not mass entertainment<br></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n<div><br></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div data-type=\"portal\"><br></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>",
